# Git Safety Rules

1. NEVER use `git push --force` unless the user explicitly approves it.
2. NEVER run `git rm -r --cached .` — this removes all files from git tracking and can cause total site outage.
3. NEVER create a folder called `app/` at the project root — Next.js will use it instead of `src/app/` and break the entire site. The real App Router code lives in `src/app/`.
4. If `git push` is rejected due to branch divergence, use `git pull --rebase` or ask the user for their preferred strategy. Never default to force push.
5. If `git push` fails or hangs in Cursor's shell, tell the user to run it in Terminal.app instead of escalating to destructive git commands.
6. Before any large git operation (rebase, cache clear, force push), run `git status` and `git ls-files --deleted`, and review staged changes to verify no files are accidentally removed.
